4.4: Edges → Adjacency List
An adjacency list stores only the neighbours of each node — much more memory efficient than
a matrix.
Rule: For each edge (u, v), append v to the list of u's neighbours. For undirected, also append
u to v's list.

a. Undirected + Unweighted
Both nodes add each other as neighbours. Store just the neighbour node.
So we write: graph[u].append(v) AND graph[v].append(u)
